packed schedules

24 July 2024

I've had many ppl come and mock me for overplanning my schedules and I never really had a good comeback to them. I agree with where they're coming from. Planning is just another way of not doing the work. And undeniably many times I have fell into the rabbithole of optomizing the system to do work but never getting work done.

"Preparing to do the thing isn't doing the thing.
Scheduling time to do the thing isn't doing the thing.
Making a to-do list for the thing isn't doing the thing.
Telling people you're going to do the thing isn't doing the thing.
Reading about how to do the thing isn't doing the thing.
The only thing that is doing the thing is doing the thing.”
— Strangest Loop

However one of my biggest problems is focus. I can't just decide to do something and do it. I wish I could, but my brain just doesn't work that way. If you're reading this there's a chance that focusing on things is hard for you as well.

The way I'm trying to get around that is by preplanning most things. I let my concentrated self plan out everything my unfocused self needs to get done. This is generally called an Ullyses Pact.

Alex Hormozi has a great definition of focus:
"Focus comes down to saying no to everything that is not what you said you would do"

Out of all the definitions of focus, this one seems the most actionable for me. Figure out a schedule that gets me closer to my goal. Then challenge yourself to get it done. You have a goal and a clear instruction manual on how to get a win today.

I'm gonna try this out for a bit, hopefully this let's me get more done or atleast give me a better picture of how I'm wasting time.
